U.S. Global Investors, Inc. (GROW) Ex-Dividend Date Scheduled for July 13, 2017


July 12, 2017, 09:00:02 AM EDT
By NASDAQ.com News









































Shutterstock photo


U.S. Global Investors, Inc. ( GROW  ) will begin trading ex-dividend on July 13, 2017. A cash dividend payment of $0.002 per share is scheduled to be paid on July 31, 2017. Shareholders who purchased GROW prior to the ex-dividend date are eligible for the cash dividend payment. This marks the 24th quarter that GROW has paid the same dividend. At the current stock price of $1.42, the dividend yield is 2.11%. The previous trading day's last sale of GROW was $1.42, representing a -38.53% decrease from the 52 week high of $2.31 and a 13.6% increase over the 52 week low of $1.25. GROW is a part of the Finance sector, which includes companies such as The Blackstone Group L.P. ( BX  ) and Franklin Resources, Inc. ( BEN  ). For more information on the declaration, record and payment dates, visit the GROW Dividend History  page. Our  Dividend Calendar  has the full list of stocks that have an ex-dividend today.



The views and opinions expressed herein are the views and opinions of the author and do not necessarily reflect those of Nasdaq, Inc.











